# Architecture Freeze

`docs/phase-b-architecture-map.md` is the frozen V1 architecture plan. Follow it unless documentation is explicitly revised first.

## Frozen decisions

| Area | Frozen value |
|------|--------------|
| Routes | `/`, `/stories`, `/stories/new`, `/stories/[id]` only |
| Auth | Supabase Auth; teachers only; `/` public landing; unauthenticated redirect to `/`; authenticated home at `/stories` |
| Persistence | Supabase; not localStorage as primary |
| Tables | `stories`, `story_pages`, `story_vocabulary`, `series_memory` (5 tables total) |
| Series Memory | Global shared singleton; updates on **save only** — not draft, not failed generation |
| Illustrations | Prompts only; one per page; copy button; no in-app image generation |
| Story shape | 12 pages; ~30–40 words per page |
| Edit scope | Text per page + regenerate from inputs |

## MUST

- Follow the architecture map for routes, data model, pipeline, and folder structure.
- Update `docs/phase-b-architecture-map.md` and affected source docs before changing frozen areas.
- Log architectural revisions in `docs/before-coding/drift-log.md`.

## MUST NOT

- Add routes (settings, export, student mode, image preview, etc.).
- Add tables or split the data model without a documentation update.
- Change Series Memory update timing, scope (global shared), or load strategy.
- Switch auth model, persistence layer, or illustration model without explicit doc revision.
- Implement features listed in architecture map section 9 (Explicit Non-Goals).

## Revision path

Document change → update `docs/before-coding/drift-log.md` → update architecture map and source docs → then implement.
